&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Kaseya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;226&quot; data-end=&quot;568&quot;&gt;Kaseya is the leading provider of AI-powered IT management and cybersecurity software, serving Managed Service Providers (MSPs) and internal IT organizations worldwide. Our comprehensive platform helps organizations efficiently manage, secure, and automate their IT environments, driving operational efficiency and long-term business success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;570&quot; data-end=&quot;898&quot;&gt;Backed by &lt;a class=&quot;decorated-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.insightpartners.com?utm_source=chatgpt.com&quot; target=&quot;_new&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;654&quot;&gt;Insight Partners&lt;/a&gt;, a leading global software investor, Kaseya has experienced sustained double-digit growth and continues to expand its global footprint. Today, Kaseya supports customers in more than 20 countries and manages over 15 million endpoints worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;900&quot; data-end=&quot;1191&quot;&gt;Founded in 2000, Kaseya has built a culture centered around innovation, accountability, and results. We are a high-growth, high-performance organization that values individuals who are driven, adaptable, and committed to delivering exceptional outcomes for our customers and teammates alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1193&quot; data-end=&quot;1468&quot;&gt;At Kaseya, success comes from embracing challenges, moving with urgency, and continuously raising the bar.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kaseya is looking for an enthusiastic, results driven and hungry&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to be at the forefront of our “land and expand” growth strategy, responsible for prospecting, nurturing, and closing new accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Business Development&lt;/strong&gt;: Lead the charge in identifying and closing new business opportunities. Manage the entire sales cycle from prospecting to closing, driving revenue by selling Kaseya&#39;s suite of solutions to potential clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage Executive-Level Decision Makers&lt;/strong&gt;: Hold discussions with CIOs, CISOs, CTOs, CCOs, and VPs, articulating the value of Kaseya’s solutions. Overcome objections, secure next steps, and ensure a successful close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Achieve Sales Targets&lt;/strong&gt;: Meet and exceed monthly, quarterly, and annual sales goals by creating value for in-house IT departments with Kaseya’s products. Own your targets and deliver results consistently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Sales Approach&lt;/strong&gt;: Work closely with internal teams such as marketing, engineering, and product specialists to leverage resources and drive sales. Use video conferencing and personalized video communication to nurture relationships and close deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity Management &amp;amp; Forecasting&lt;/strong&gt;: Track opportunities throughout the sales process, ensuring strong Salesforce (SF.com) hygiene and accurate forecasting. Participate in account reviews with management and teams to strategize for success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Experience&lt;/strong&gt;: Provide a professional and seamless sales experience, from initial meetings to post-sale follow-ups, ensuring that all prospects have a positive and efficient experience with Kaseya.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Campaigns &amp;amp; Programs&lt;/strong&gt;: Participate in ad-hoc sales campaigns to help create new prospects and opportunities, contributing to Kaseya’s growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of sales

